Definition of Pest Control
Pest control refers to the management and regulation of pest populations, which includes insects, rodents, weeds, and other organisms that can harm human health, agriculture, and the environment. This field encompasses a variety of methods and strategies to eliminate or mitigate pest infestations, ensuring the safety and health of communities, the integrity of food supplies, and the preservation of structures and landscapes. Pest control can be divided into several categories, including chemical, biological, physical, and cultural control methods.
Pest Control Market is expected to grow from USD 23.5 billion in 2023-e to USD 34.2 billion by 2030, at a CAGR of 5.5% during the forecast period.
